            <ChoiceText>The forge was a massive building, but even it could not contain the endless halls and galleries that exist inside it.  Throughout cyclopean crystal pillars jut up into the higher levels.  They begin straight and nearly as thick as a house and gradually become finer and more delicate, eventually forming a sharp latticework around the forge's central chamber.

In the center of the chamber there is a silver platform etched with astronomical symbols.  When you stand on it you feel the complete power of Elemental running through you.  You feel Procipinee straining to keep the way into the forge open and through that whole into the world you can feel every shard, every spell and everyone who can wield magic.  With the slightest effort you pull the power of the fallen sovereigns from them.

The chamber erupts with attackers, the protectors of Elemental rebelling at your grip on the heart of the world.  You would have been crushed once, but now you are a god.</ChoiceText>
