            <AutoFulfillSuccessConditionsOnSetup>1</AutoFulfillSuccessConditionsOnSetup>
            <ChoiceText>You attempt to teleport through the gate.  But it takes more concentration to jump between worlds and Procipinee has only to release her effort to close the gate.

As it closes you send a single bolt of dark fire through.  Your last view of Elemental is the form of Queen Procipinee falling to the ground dead.</ChoiceText>
            <ChoiceMedallion>Q_ProcipineeFalls.png</ChoiceMedallion>
            <ChoiceMedallionFrame>Medallion_Frame_17.png</ChoiceMedallionFrame>
            <QuestChoiceDef>
                <Description>...</Description>
                <NextObjectiveID>9</NextObjectiveID>
            </QuestChoiceDef>
        </QuestObjectiveDef>
        <QuestObjectiveDef>
            <ObjectiveID>8</ObjectiveID>
            <AutoFulfillSuccessConditionsOnSetup>1</AutoFulfillSuccessConditionsOnSetup>
            <ChoiceText>You reach out to Elemental and find the corrupted form of Shirayn.  You feel her pain and savage anger, which is so unlike her spirit in life.  Deep within her demonic form some part of her still lives.  Though you expect dark chains to bind her, there are none.  The corruption has no power of its own, it only fractured what was there like a mirror broken into sharp shards.  Piece by piece you restore her spirit.  When it is done you nod at Procipinee and she closes the gate.  Somewhere far off, in a different world than the one you now occupy, Shirayne is waking up as if from a long nightmare.</ChoiceText>
            <ChoiceMedallion>Q_ShiryaneRestored.png</ChoiceMedallion>
            <ChoiceMedallionFrame>Medallion_Frame_17.png</ChoiceMedallionFrame>
            <QuestChoiceDef>
                <Description>...</Description>
                <NextObjectiveID>9</NextObjectiveID>
            </QuestChoiceDef>
        </QuestObjectiveDef>
