        <Description>Once this may have been a bustling inn where traders haggled and sailors enjoyed a night on land.  But those days are long past.  Now seedy men whisper, drink and gamble in the dark corners of the great room.  You spent your youth in such places, and you wonder if it disgusts you now because these men are wasting their lives, or because you wasted so much of yours.</Description>
